The four types of holoprosencephaly are:
1. Complete or classic holoprosencephaly, which is characterized by a single, undivided forebrain;
2. Partial or hemicoronal holoprosencephaly, which is characterized by a partially divided forebrain;
3. Semi-holoprosencephaly, which is characterized by a partially divided forebrain and a single, undivided midbrain;
4. Heterotopic brains, which is characterized by the presence of two or more, usually malformed, brains in the same cranial cavity.
